SIMPLE: hilum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hilum
<hw>Hi"lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a little thing,
trifle.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The eye of a bean or
other seed; the mark or scar at the point of attachment of an ovule or
seed to its base or support; -- called also
<altname>hile</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The part of a gland, or similar
organ, where the blood vessels and nerves enter; the hilus; <as>as, the
<ex>hilum</ex> of the kidney</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hilus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
